sentences: Anthony Aaron Lines (born November 17, 1977) is a Canadian country musician.
Aaron Lines' debut album, Love Changes Everything, was released in Canada in 2001 by independent record label Combustion Music.
Lines was nominated for Best New Country Artist/Group at the 2002 Juno Awards, and Best New Artist at the 2002 Canadian Country Music Association (CCMA) Awards.
Lines was nominated for Best New Country Artist/Group at the 2002 Juno Awards, and Best New Artist at the 2002 Canadian Country Music Association (CCMA) Awards.
He performed a showcase for RCA Nashville in May 2001.
The next day, the label phoned to offer Lines a record deal.
He immediately began work on his debut album, Living Out Loud, released on January 7, 2003.
The album was a success in Canada as well, and at the 2003 CCMA Awards, Lines received six nominations, including the Kraft Cheez Whiz Fans' Choice Award.
When the awards were handed out in September, Lines was named Male Artist of the Year, and also picked up the Rising Star Award.
When the awards were handed out in September, Lines was named Male Artist of the Year, and also picked up the Rising Star Award.
In 2003, Lines was an opening act for Martina McBride's Greatest Hits tour.
Aaron Lines' second album, Waitin' on the Wonderful, was released on September 6, 2005.
